projects.name: Shared Wheels
projects.description: Developed a carpooling platform using React.js, Node.js, and MongoDB to connect commuters based on proximity and schedule. Implemented secure user authentication, ride booking, and profile management, emphasizing privacy and ease of use. Contributed to reducing urban congestion and carbon footprints through community-based ride-sharing.

projects.name: Pharmacy Management System
projects.description: This project involves the implementation of a Pharmacy Management System using MySQL for database storage, NetBeans IDE, and Tomcat server for web application development. Utilizing HTML and CSS for web design. This system aims to provide a convenient solution for customers to access medication information and make purchases without visiting physical pharmacies. It offers comprehensive details on medicines, including costs and usage, enhancing accessibility and convenience for users.

experiences.description: Developed strong data analysis skills at APSSDC, including visualization, cleaning, and sorting, through immersive training and hands-on experience. Led a screen time analysis project, leveraging data processing and analysis to gain insights and improve efficiency by 25% while successfully managing the project.
